                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6 flex items-baseline gap-1">
              <span class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-amber-300">$0</span>
              <span class="text-slate-400">/month</span>
            </div>

            <ul class="mt-6 space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <%= honey_icon(:shield, classes: "h-4 w-4 text-amber-400") %>
                <span class="text-slate-300">1 active honeypot</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <%= honey_icon(:server, classes: "h-4 w-4 text-amber-400") %>
                <span class="text-slate-300">All core platform features</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <%= honey_icon(:bell, classes: "h-4 w-4 text-amber-400") %>
                <span class="text-slate-300">Email alert notifications</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <%= honey_icon(:ticket, classes: "h-4 w-4 text-amber-400") %>
                <span class="text-slate-300">Basic email support</span>
              </li>
            </ul>

            <p class="mt-auto pt-4 text-xs text-slate-400">
              No credit card required. Just create your account and deploy your first honeypot.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact Sales -->
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900 p-8 shadow-sm">
          <div class="flex h-full flex-col">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="inline-flex rounded-xl bg-amber-500/15 p-3 text-amber-300">
                <%= honey_icon(:mail, classes: "h-6 w-6") %>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">Need more than one?</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
                  If you need multiple honeypots, larger environments or a tailored deployment,
                  our team can help you design the right plan.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6 text-sm text-slate-300">
              Tell us about your infrastructure size, number of sites and expected number of decoys.
              We’ll propose a simple subscription aligned with your use case.
            </div>

            <div class="mt-auto pt-4">
              <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
                <button
                  type="button"
                  class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-amber-500 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-950 shadow hover:bg-amber-400"
                  onclick="openContactSalesModal()"
                >
                  Contact Sales
                </button>
                <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">
                  Prefer another channel? You can also reach us via the contact section below.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="py-20 scroll-mt-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="mx-auto mb-10 max-w-3xl text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-4xl">
          Frequently asked questions
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-4xl gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <% [
          {
            q: "What hypervisors does the .ova support?",
            a: "Any OVA-compatible hypervisor such as VMware Workstation, ESXi, Proxmox, and Oracle VirtualBox."
          },
          {
            q: "Can I run on a static IP?",
            a: "Yes. You can configure either DHCP or a static IP directly from the VM console during initial setup."
          },
          {
            q: "How does the pairing token work?",
            a: "On first boot, the honeypot generates a unique pairing token displayed on the console. Paste it into HoneyOps when creating a new honeypot, and the agent will automatically link to your account."
          },
          {
            q: "What notifications will I receive?",
            a: "You can configure email notifications for incidents and health checks. You may also set maintenance windows to temporarily pause notifications during planned work."
          },
          {
            q: "Is there an API?",
            a: "A public JSON API is coming soon. It will allow you to automate honeypot provisioning, manage policies, and pull incidents into your existing security tooling."
          },
          {
            q: "Do honeypots auto-update?",
            a: "Yes. Honeypots periodically check for new agent versions and can update automatically, or you may choose manual updates from the dashboard."
          },
          {
            q: "What data does the honeypot collect?",
            a: "Only security-related interaction data and minimal operational metadata. No legitimate network traffic or internal system data is collected."
          },
          {
            q: "Are honeypots monitored?",
            a: "Yes. If a honeypot is detected as disconnected or unresponsive, HoneyOps immediately triggers an alert so you can verify the cause and ensure it is not related to a potential intrusion."
          }
        ].each do |item| %>
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-100"><%= item[:q] %></h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300"><%= item[:a] %></p>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer id="contact" class="border-t border-slate-900 bg-slate-950 py-12 text-sm">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">

      <!-- Top part: left 40% + right 60% -->
      <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-5">

        <!-- LEFT: HoneyOps blurb (40%) -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-2">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-slate-100">
            <span class="text-amber-400"><%= honey_icon(:shield, classes: "h-5 w-5") %></span>
            <span class="font-semibold">HoneyOps</span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300 text-base max-w-md">
            Honeypots as a Service. Built for fast, reliable deception at any scale.
